OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
Trent Boult bowling to Naman Dhir, BOULT STRIKES TWICE   AND MI ARE IN A PRECARIOUS POSITION   good length ball, pitching on off stump, Naman Dhir Attempting a flick, he misses, and the ball hits the pad, prompting a confident appeal from RR, which the umpire upholds. MI's No. 3 consults Kishan before opting for a review. The initial check confirms a fair delivery, and Ultra-Edge clears any bat involvement. Ball-tracking reveals the pitch and impact are in line, with the wicket's fate hanging on the umpire's call. Dhir, unfortunately, must make his way back. This marks the 24th occasion Trent Boult has claimed a wicket in the opening over of an IPL match.

WICKET Naman Dhir lbw Trent Boult (Mumbai Indians 1 Runs for 2 wickets)
